1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,628
[Marcus] <i>He developed</i>
<i>post-traumatic stress disorder.</i>

2
00:00:03,712 --> 00:00:08,258
I owe Sir Rustia a great debt
because he saved my son's life.

3
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:11,261
[Ramli] <i>So when we found out</i>
<i>he was still alive, I immediately hid him.</i>

4
00:00:11,344 --> 00:00:14,764
I know my fellow villagers
will never easily forgive any of you.

5
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:16,683
[Ramli] <i>So if I were you, I'd leave now.</i>

6
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:20,311
I'm not leaving
until I find out what really happened.

7
00:00:20,395 --> 00:00:23,440
[Ramli] <i>You came here</i>
<i>and slaughtered my fellow villagers!</i>

8
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:26,067
Another group started
the chaos that night.

9
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:28,778
But you still came to arrest Datu Rahman!

10
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:31,156
[Marcus] <i>He has to face</i>
<i>gun smuggling charges.</i>

11
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:33,074
Those accusations against him aren't true!

12
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,492
[Ramli] <i>You want proof?</i>

13
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:35,994
He didn't want to give it
to the authorities

14
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,954
because he no longer knows
which police officers

15
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,622
are protecting the syndicates.

16
00:00:39,706 --> 00:00:41,624
How's your search for Datu Rahman going?

17
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:42,959
[in English] I'm still working on it, Dad.

18
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:45,587
[Manuel, in English]
So you've got nothing?

19
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:48,089
[in English] When will you stop
disappointing me?!

20
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:50,800
You don't have to do this alone.
I can help you.

21
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:54,262
[in English] Whenever you're around,
people end up dead.

22
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,849
[Jalil] <i>I can't read General Carillo.</i>

23
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:01,895
<i>But what if he noticed</i>
<i>that I'm hiding something?</i>

24
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:03,354
[Jalil] Doctor.

25
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:04,773
[Teresa] <i>Thank you so much.</i>

26
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:06,149
Come have dinner at the house.

27
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:09,110
Come on. Let me make it up to you.

28
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,820
Alright, ma'am. If that's what you want.

29
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,491
[Marcus] <i>I'll fix what needs to be fixed.</i>

30
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:19,329
<i>I'll make sure I find out</i>
<i>who's behind all of this.</i>

31
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:29,839
[mysterious theme music playing]

32
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:42,644
- [pensive music playing]
- [sniffles]

33
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,948
[tense music playing]

34
00:01:55,031 --> 00:01:58,409
[tense music continues]

35
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:00,245
[Usman] <i>Marcus!</i>

36
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:01,788
Brother, where are you going?

37
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,833
I just need to go back to the island.

38
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,000
What?

39
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:08,294
Brother, I won't get anything out of this

40
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:10,505
if I just wait for Datu Rahman to confess.

41
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:13,049
[Marcus] <i>I need to find another way.</i>

42
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,552
[tense music continues]

43
00:02:15,635 --> 00:02:17,804
If you don't want to talk to Marcus…

44
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:22,183
then talk to me.

45
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:25,812
Muslim to Muslim.

46
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:29,190
[exhales deeply]

47
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:32,318
What exactly is your secret, Datu Rahman?

48
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:35,280
Too many innocent people
are getting dragged into this.

49
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,073
You're a Muslim too.

50
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:41,452
We both know we're blamed for everything,

51
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:43,413
even when we're innocent.

52
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:46,291
So if you truly are innocent,

53
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:49,419
tell me and Marcus everything you know,

54
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,881
so we can help clear your name.

55
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:59,178
I don't trust that Marcus.

56
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,390
So if you trust him,

57
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:05,351
then I can't trust you either.

58
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:07,478
Why?

59
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,815
Because you're afraid of something?

60
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:13,276
Or maybe because
you're protecting someone?

61
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:16,154
[exhales deeply]

62
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:17,322
- This.
- [inhales]

63
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,032
This man…

64
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:25,872
Marcus fought him on the island before.

65
00:03:27,081 --> 00:03:30,543
And even now, he keeps running into him.

66
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:33,379
Because of his search for you.

67
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:36,132
Who is he?

68
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:40,553
[dramatic flourish]

69
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:46,142
Is he the one who helped you escape
during the transfer?

70
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,521
- [cop] Move! Move!
- [protesters] Justice! Justice!

71
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:52,357
- Justice!
- Out of the way!

72
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:57,237
[overlapping clamor]

73
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,821
- [man] Stop!
- [gunshots]

74
00:03:58,905 --> 00:03:59,948
[overlapping clamor]

75
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:02,283
- [man 1] Usman!
- [man 2] Move!

76
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,703
[protesters] Justice! Justice! Justice!

77
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:10,583
[tense music continues]

78
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:13,920
[men grunting]

79
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:16,339
Let me go! That's enough!

80
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:18,299
[Jalil] Father!

81
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:21,386
[Usman] He's important to you.

82
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:26,724
[music intensifies]

83
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:31,062
Do you know that while
you're hiding here in silence,

84
00:04:31,562 --> 00:04:33,898
this man's life is in danger?

85
00:04:34,482 --> 00:04:36,192
He's wanted by the police

86
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:38,945
because they're accusing him
of being your accomplice.

87
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:42,073
So if you want to save this man,

88
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:48,663
Datu Rahman, tell us everything you know.

89
00:04:48,746 --> 00:04:53,501
[tense music concludes]

90
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:57,463
[crickets chirping]

91
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:03,553
There's no house here.
Is this pinned address correct?

92
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:06,723
[crickets chirping]

93
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,487
Hello, ma'am?

94
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:23,823
I'm already here.

95
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,411
[gate creaks]

96
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:35,793
[unsettling music playing]

97
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:58,399
[engine starts]

98
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:05,073
[unsettling music continues]

99
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:12,580
[pensive music playing]

100
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:24,717
Doc, this is delicious.

101
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:26,803
- Did you really cook this yourself?
- Mm-hm!

102
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:29,472
- Just keep eating.
- Yes, ma'am.

103
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:38,940
You and Marcus are actually alike.
You both like vegetables.

104
00:06:39,023 --> 00:06:41,734
Those are his favorite. Him and…

105
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,862
[Teresa breathes heavily]

106
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,657
Him and…

107
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:49,325
[breathes shakily]

108
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:53,162
Marcus was a picky eater
when he was a child,

109
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,914
but when it came to vegetables…

110
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,541
[breathes heavily]

111
00:06:56,624 --> 00:07:00,044
Doc, are you okay?

112
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:04,590
[sobs] I'm sorry, okay?

113
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:09,220
I just remembered…

114
00:07:11,848 --> 00:07:13,850
my other son…

115
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,811
Gabriel.

116
00:07:18,062 --> 00:07:22,567
[morose music playing]

117
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:24,777
Gabriel?

118
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:33,327
Marcus, why did you let
your brother wander off?

119
00:07:33,411 --> 00:07:34,871
Now he got hurt because he fell.

120
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,873
He's too hyper, Mom.

121
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:40,460
Son… I'm going to be busy
with the medical mission,

122
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:43,171
so I'm counting on you
to watch over your brother.

123
00:07:43,254 --> 00:07:46,966
If Dad didn't leave us,
then I wouldn't have to watch him.

124
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:49,594
But your father already left us.

125
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:51,679
And there's nothing we can do about that.

126
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:55,641
At least you got to spend
some time with your father.

127
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:58,561
Gabriel was still very little
when your father left.

128
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:02,440
He never got to experience
what it's like to have a father.

129
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:06,235
He's my youngest. [sniffles]

130
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:08,070
He's been gone for a long time.

131
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,365
Thirty years already.

132
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:18,039
[morose music continues]

133
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:21,542
[boat engine humming]

134
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:26,631
That's why you were his idol.

135
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:30,009
Sorry, son, okay?

136
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,762
I know things are hard for you,

137
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:35,640
and I'm dragging you both
along on trips like this.

138
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:40,019
But I really don't have anyone else
to leave the two of you with.

139
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:45,024
That's why I'm trusting you
to take care of your brother.

140
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,653
Can you do that for me, son?

141
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:50,780
- [sighs]
- [young Teresa] Hmm?

142
00:08:56,160 --> 00:09:00,998
[Marcus] <i>Gabriel,</i>
<i>you're my inspiration in everything I do.</i>

143
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,126
<i>I want to save people.</i>

144
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:07,922
<i>Because that's the one thing</i>
<i>I wasn't able to do for you.</i>

145
00:09:10,424 --> 00:09:11,551
Gabriel?

146
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:16,556
Gabriel!

147
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:19,225
Are you awake?

148
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:21,352
Gabriel!

149
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:24,689
Gabriel!

150
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:30,695
[clicks tongue] Mom's gonna get mad
at me again because of this.

151
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,615
[groans]

152
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:37,535
[alarm blaring]

153
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:38,786
Gabriel!

154
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,998
- Gabriel!
- I'm here, brother!

155
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:44,083
- [Gabriel crying]
- Gabriel!

156
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,335
- Gabriel!
- [crying] Marcus!

157
00:09:47,336 --> 00:09:50,298
[Gabriel crying]

158
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:53,384
Gabriel, don't be scared.
I'll take care of you!

159
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,596
- Yes, brother.
- Let's go!

160
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,889
[Gabriel crying]

161
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:01,767
[alarm blaring]

162
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:03,060
[Marcus] Let's go!

163
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:09,525
- [young Marcus] Hurry!
- [Gabriel crying]

164
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:11,527
[Gabriel] Marcus!

165
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:14,071
[young Marcus] Let's go. This way! Hurry!

166
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:17,825
[alarm blaring]

167
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:19,827
- [Gabriel crying]
- [gasps]

168
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,331
Gabriel, don't let go!

169
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:24,707
Just hold on!

170
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:29,879
[ominous music playing]

171
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:30,963
Marcus!

172
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,424
- [screams]
- Marcus!

173
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:36,886
[thunder roars]

174
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:44,143
[sobbing softly]

175
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,355
[sobs]

176
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:50,358
[morose music playing]

177
00:10:50,441 --> 00:10:52,401
I'm sorry, okay? [sniffles]

178
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:55,112
I know it's been a long time, but…

179
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:58,157
[sighs, sniffles]

180
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,450
Doc.

181
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:00,576
‪[soft sobs]

182
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:03,621
It's okay.

183
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:09,293
They say that when
we lose the people we love…

184
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,421
[Teresa sniffles]

185
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:17,385
…the pain never really goes away.

186
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:19,387
We just learn to live with it.

187
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:21,972
Maybe that's true.

188
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:24,350
That's why…

189
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:28,938
I can't stop feeling sad
whenever I remember my son.

190
00:11:29,021 --> 00:11:30,022
[Teresa sniffles]

191
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:33,818
[morose music playing]

192
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:43,285
- [Marcus crying]
- Sir!

193
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:45,621
Sir, where's my son, Gabriel?

194
00:11:45,704 --> 00:11:46,622
Doc, I'm sorry.

195
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:48,999
We didn't find any child
matching your description.

196
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,876
What are you saying? Where's my son?

197
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,420
- Doc, we already did everything we could.
- Where is my son?

198
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,588
Where's my son, Gabriel?!

199
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:56,757
- I'm really sorry.
- Gabriel!

200
00:11:56,841 --> 00:11:57,967
[young Teresa] <i>Gabriel!</i>

201
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:01,762
<i>Gabriel! Why didn't you find him?!</i>

202
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:05,724
[young Marcus] <i>I'm sorry, Mom! I'm sorry!</i>

203
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:07,852
[crying]

204
00:12:07,935 --> 00:12:08,769
[sobbing]

205
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,062
I keep wondering

206
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,150
what he would be like now
if he were still alive.

207
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:16,944
If he were here with me.

208
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:24,243
[morose music continues]

209
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:28,414
[sobs]

210
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:34,462
Doc, I understand you.

211
00:12:35,463 --> 00:12:41,760
Sometimes, I also think about my family.

212
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,180
My real family.

213
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:48,851
Real family?

214
00:12:50,853 --> 00:12:52,354
I'm adopted, Doc.

215
00:12:53,230 --> 00:13:00,154
[pensive music playing]

216
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:05,910
[morose music playing]

217
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,502
[sobbing] Jalil, my son.

218
00:13:22,259 --> 00:13:23,677
[panting]

219
00:13:29,558 --> 00:13:31,602
[man] Help! Help!

220
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,354
Help!

221
00:13:34,396 --> 00:13:35,314
[woman] Allah.

222
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:41,111
What happened? What happened?

223
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,112
Oh no…

224
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,365
[melancholic music playing]

225
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:45,574
[cries quietly]

226
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:48,911
[inhales, exhales deeply]

227
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:56,585
How are you feeling?

228
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:03,926
[melancholic music continues]

229
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:15,396
[melancholic music playing]

230
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:24,738
[melancholic music continues]

231
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:27,074
What's your name?

232
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:43,632
[melancholic music continues]

233
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,760
Hasan. Hasan…

234
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:50,180
Hasan, please don't go!

235
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,225
Don't you see?

236
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:55,561
The boy needs you!

237
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:57,563
He loves you!

238
00:14:57,646 --> 00:15:00,441
I don't deserve his love.

239
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,236
Because I'm part of the reason
why he can't remember anything,

240
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,863
why he's all alone now.

241
00:15:05,946 --> 00:15:08,782
But you're trying to be
a good person, aren't you?

242
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,784
The child has no family left.

243
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:14,747
Wouldn't it be a greater sin
if we abandoned him?

244
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,333
At a time when he needs you most?

245
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:21,921
There are a lot of bad people after me.

246
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,380
He'll just get dragged into my mess.

247
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:26,425
You said you want to turn over a new leaf.

248
00:15:27,009 --> 00:15:28,552
You can do that here.

249
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:30,346
We will protect you.

250
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:32,431
Change your name.

251
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:37,227
[melancholic music continues]

252
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:50,741
Rahman.

253
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,371
Rahman Abubakar.

254
00:15:55,454 --> 00:16:01,919
[melancholic music continues]

255
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:08,092
[young Gabriel whimpering]

256
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:13,055
[young Gabriel sniffling]

257
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:16,475
Please don't leave me.

258
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,942
[young Datu Rahman] Ah.

259
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:29,989
Forgive me.

260
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:34,827
I promise you this.
I will never leave you.

261
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:38,706
[young Gabriel] Father…

262
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:41,375
[both sobbing]

263
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:46,046
[melancholic music continues]

264
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:57,016
I don't know anything about…

265
00:16:58,434 --> 00:16:59,935
my real family.

266
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:05,107
But I think about them sometimes.

267
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:09,403
I wonder if they're still alive.

268
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:15,409
If they, uh… think of me, too.

269
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:16,577
[sniffles]

270
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,954
If they're still looking for me.

271
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,251
But, Doc, I can tell you this.

272
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:25,335
[sniffles]

273
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:28,005
I never felt like I was missing something.

274
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:31,925
[melancholic music continues]

275
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:35,054
I owe that to the family
who took care of me.

276
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:45,481
[in Tausug] I name this child
as Jalil Abubakar.

277
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:46,690
[in Arabic] God willing.

278
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:49,735
Jalil.

279
00:17:50,527 --> 00:17:51,653
My son.

280
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,991
Father… Father!

281
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:59,286
[Rahman, young Jalil chuckling]

282
00:17:59,369 --> 00:18:02,372
[Jalil] Not once did they
make me feel that…

283
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,584
I was different.

284
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:07,377
That I wasn't family.

285
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:09,922
[Jamilah] Brother Jalil!

286
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,093
[Jalil] Father.

287
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:16,929
[soft chuckle]

288
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:22,017
They've loved me so much.

289
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:25,687
[melancholic music continues]

290
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:28,941
and that's why I'm forever
grateful to them, Doc.

291
00:18:30,859 --> 00:18:34,279
I'll give back all the love
they've given me.

292
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:37,825
I'll protect them.

293
00:18:38,325 --> 00:18:39,576
[sniffles]

294
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:44,998
They're my source of strength
and inspiration in everything I do.

295
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:48,502
[Teresa sniffles]

296
00:18:48,585 --> 00:18:50,671
Oh, look at us. We both ended up in tears.

297
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:52,673
[sniffling]

298
00:18:55,008 --> 00:18:57,386
We're too dramatic, Doc.

299
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:59,012
[chuckles softly]

300
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,014
[sniffles]

301
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,308
[sniffles, exhales softly]

302
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:07,479
[melancholic music continues]

303
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:18,657
[Marcus] <i>Mark my words.</i>
<i>I'll solve this case.</i>

304
00:19:19,491 --> 00:19:22,452
<i>No one will ever fall victim</i>
<i>to their hands again.</i>

305
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:28,709
[melancholic music continues]

306
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,808
I'll be on my way, Doc.

307
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:46,518
[crickets chirping]

308
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:47,978
Until next time, alright?

309
00:19:50,355 --> 00:19:53,650
Since you mentioned being alone at home,

310
00:19:53,734 --> 00:19:56,528
whenever you don't feel like cooking,
you can always eat with us.

311
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,448
Think of this place as your second home.

312
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:05,621
I will. Thank you.

313
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:08,999
Be careful, son.

314
00:20:12,669 --> 00:20:16,089
[tender music playing]

315
00:20:16,173 --> 00:20:17,341
Same to you.

316
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:21,637
Take care.

317
00:20:24,556 --> 00:20:26,141
[keys jingling]

318
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:28,060
[car door clicks open]

319
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:36,068
[engine starts]

320
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:40,530
[tender music continues]

321
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:05,180
[pensive music playing]

322
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:24,199
[Teresa] <i>I just remembered…</i>

323
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,994
my other son.

324
00:21:28,578 --> 00:21:29,955
Gabriel.

325
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:33,417
[Teresa] <i>My youngest.</i>

326
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:35,961
<i>He's been missing for a long time.</i>

327
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,422
It's been 30 years.

328
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:41,675
[Teresa] <i>So here I am.</i>

329
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:46,596
I always get sad whenever I think of him.

330
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:51,184
[pensive music continues]

331
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,478
I wonder…

332
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:57,482
where he is now, whether he's still alive.

333
00:21:58,817 --> 00:22:00,235
I picture myself with him.

334
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:10,787
[phone buzzing]

335
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:14,541
Jamilah? Why? Is something wrong?

336
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:15,917
Jalil…

337
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:19,087
Rashid said he has something
important to tell you.

338
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,758
- [in Tausug] About what?
- [Jamilah, in Tausug] I don't know.

339
00:22:23,258 --> 00:22:24,676
He didn't want to say.

340
00:22:25,218 --> 00:22:28,847
[Jamilah] <i>He said it'd be best</i>
<i>if you discussed it in person.</i>

341
00:22:28,930 --> 00:22:30,807
Jalil, it seems to be very important.

342
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:33,560
Okay, Jamilah. Thank you.
I'll take care of it.

343
00:22:33,643 --> 00:22:39,566
[pensive music continues]

344
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:58,168
[unsettling music playing]

345
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:13,266
Any updates on the task I gave you?

346
00:23:15,143 --> 00:23:16,728
We followed the Muslim.

347
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:19,272
That Usman Sabdani.

348
00:23:19,356 --> 00:23:21,108
You're right, ma'am.

349
00:23:21,191 --> 00:23:23,360
He meets up with Marcus Reyes.

350
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:26,613
They always go to this abandoned place.

351
00:23:27,197 --> 00:23:28,532
They seem to be hiding something.

352
00:23:28,615 --> 00:23:30,200
Datu Rahman.

353
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:34,704
What do you want us to do?

354
00:23:36,081 --> 00:23:37,290
[Lara sighs]

355
00:23:37,874 --> 00:23:42,796
[breathing heavily]

356
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,759
[cries quietly]

357
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:57,435
[music becomes suspenseful]

358
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:13,285
You wanted to speak with me?

359
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:17,873
[suspenseful music continues]

360
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:20,917
I saw Usman coming out of some house.

361
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:23,336
As far as I know, he doesn't live there.

362
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:26,047
He was acting suspiciously.

363
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:28,633
He was very cautious,

364
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,303
as if he was afraid
that someone would see him.

365
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:35,432
What's even more bizarre is that

366
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:39,895
I saw Marcus Reyes exiting
the same house the other night.

367
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:46,151
- Are you sure?
- Yes, I'm sure.

368
00:24:46,735 --> 00:24:48,653
There was something different
to that house.

369
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:52,157
People who go to places like that

370
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:55,285
always have something to hide.

371
00:24:55,368 --> 00:24:57,871
[suspenseful music continues]

372
00:24:57,954 --> 00:25:01,666
Could it be them who abducted
and are keeping Father hidden?

373
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:03,627
That's my suspicion too,

374
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:07,380
which is why I called Jamilah,
so I could talk to you.

375
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:15,472
[suspenseful music continues]

376
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:24,856
Here's the address.

377
00:25:27,692 --> 00:25:31,696
[suspenseful music playing]

378
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:34,407
If there's anything else I can do
for you and your family,

379
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:36,243
just let me know.

380
00:25:38,036 --> 00:25:39,704
You've already helped us a lot.

381
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,623
You might get into trouble.

382
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:46,336
[sniffles] Come on now.
You know we have each other's back.

383
00:25:48,755 --> 00:25:49,881
[in Tausug] Thank you.

384
00:25:51,841 --> 00:25:54,010
[suspenseful music continues]

385
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:55,887
[tires screeching]

386
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:07,440
- [gunshot]
- [lock clanks]

387
00:26:07,524 --> 00:26:09,401
[suspenseful music continues]

388
00:26:16,866 --> 00:26:17,993
[man] Check there!

389
00:26:20,328 --> 00:26:21,329
Nothing here, Boss!

390
00:26:22,289 --> 00:26:26,835
[suspenseful music continues]

391
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:34,467
[man] <i>Get in!</i>

392
00:26:37,512 --> 00:26:40,432
- [man] <i>Ma'am, we've got Datu Rahman.</i>
- [in English] Good.

393
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:43,643
[man] <i>Hurry up! The boss is coming!</i>

394
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:45,937
Now that Datu Rahman is gone,

395
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:48,273
nothing stands in the way
of the weapon delivery.

396
00:26:48,356 --> 00:26:51,401
- [gunshots]
- [groans]

397
00:26:51,484 --> 00:26:53,153
[Datu Rahman] <i>I don't know anything!</i>

398
00:26:53,236 --> 00:26:55,405
You'll get nothing out of me.

399
00:26:55,905 --> 00:26:58,283
[groans]

400
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:00,994
[man] <i>Ma'am, we're under attack here!</i>

401
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:02,746
Don't let him get away!

402
00:27:02,829 --> 00:27:04,664
Don't let them get Datu Rahman!

403
00:27:04,748 --> 00:27:06,583
- [gunshots]
- [man] <i>You think you've won?</i>

404
00:27:06,666 --> 00:27:10,045
No matter how many times
these weapons are confiscated,

405
00:27:10,128 --> 00:27:11,546
they will always
find their way back to us.

406
00:27:11,629 --> 00:27:17,802
[groans]

407
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:21,848
[dramatic music playing]
